Privacy Policy
Last updated October 2024
We are
District5 Ltd
, a company registered with Companies House in England and Wales under number 09960097, whose registered office is at Clifton House, Four Elms Road, Cardiff, S. Wales, United Kingdom, CF24 1LE ("District5"/"we"/"us"/"our").
We provide the Traffic Panic franchise of games ("Games") that can be accessed through the website www.trafficpanic.com, or through the Apple Game Store, or the Google Pay Store.
Because you use the Website www.trafficpanic.com (the "Website") and/or our Games, we process your personal information in accordance with this Privacy Policy (the "Policy"). This is part of the contractual framework you enter into while downloading and using the Games and/or the Websites (together as the "Services"). It specifies the legal basis upon which we process your personal information as data controller.
We are committed to protecting and respecting your privacy and your data rights. If you have any questions or comments about this Privacy Policy, you can contact the data protection officer (DPO) we designated for this purpose at
gdpr@district5.co.uk
So, let’s describe what this Policy tells you. It explains:
what information we may collect about you;
what we may do with the information we collect about you;
whether we share your information with anyone else;
the types of cookies we use and how you can reject these cookies;
where we store your information;
how we keep your information secure; and
the rights you have regarding the personal information you have provided to us
THIS IS WHAT WE DO WITH THE INFORMATION WE COLLECT ABOUT YOU
1.
The information we collect to correspond with you
If you contact us (by phone, email, through the Website, a Game or Discord) as part of our contractual relationship, we can collect and store several pieces of information about you (name, address, telephone number and/or email address).
We use the data you provide to correspond with you and we keep it in case we need to contact you in the future in relation to the issue for which you contacted us.
We may keep a record of that for one year after our last contact with you. If you report a problem with the Website or a Game, we may keep that information for the same duration.
This information is intended for us only and will not, under any circumstances, be sold or leased to third parties. This data may, however, be communicated to third-party technical service providers, solely for the purpose explained above.
2.
The information we collect to provide you the Services when you use our Games
When you play our Games, we collect IT tracking information from you, which may include:
a pseudonymous identifier to identify you;
any preferences that you have selected;
performance related data (such as scores and achievements);
device information (such as your operating system, locale, version, device model and capabilities/specifications of the device);
session information (how long you play our Games for);
connection type (for example, WiFi, 3G, 4G);
which Games you are playing or have played previously and attempts within those Games;
mac address;
network service provider;
approximate location (city and country based off of your IP address);
IP address;
locale information (such as country, time zone and language);
device advertising identifier (this is a unique identifier, that identifies your device, but not related to any personally identifiable information);
purchase information (to let us know what you purchased,
no
payment details are collected);
date and time of your first launch of a Game
advertising information (such as how many adverts you have seen while playing our Games)
We collect this personal information to:
provide you the Services
ensure that you are a real person and not a robot;
help us identify any errors in our Games and make your experience better and more personal. By collecting analytical information about your continued participation in the Game, we can determine whether the change is worthwhile and whether it improves your overall experience with our Games.
help us identify which group of users are most active in our Game. This includes but is not limited to: country, gender, age range (not an exact age, but a range. For example, 20 to 24 years old), device manufacturer and operating system information, etc.
We may retain this information for one year after our last contact with you.
This information is for our use only and will not be sold or rented to any third party. This data may, however, be communicated to or by third party technical service providers, solely for the purpose of providing the service.
3.
The information used in relation to advertising
Our Games are primarily funded by advertising. To do this, we use several third-party advertising companies to provide you with applicable in-game advertisements.
We use a device ID called an IDFA for advertising purposes and allow third parties such as social networks (see comprehensive list in the table below) to drop a file called SDK on your device while using the Game, which enables them, if you agree, to display personalized advertising while you are using the Game.
Third party IDFAs/SDKs are deposited under the contract, but their use by third party publishers to provide targeted advertising is subject to consent.
Where we propose using your personal information for any other uses, we ensure that we notify and if needed, ask for your consent first. You will also be given the opportunity to withhold or withdraw your consent for the use of your personal information for purposes described in this point.
