THIS IS WHO ELSE WE SHARE YOUR INFORMATION WITH
We may disclose your personal information to third parties, but only in the ways that are described in this policy:
if we are under a duty to disclose or share your personal information in order to comply with any legal or regulatory obligation or request;
to enforce or apply our terms of use/terms and conditions and other agreements or to investigate potential breaches; or
to protect the rights, property or safety of our Services, or our users.
if we are involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets. If such an event occurs, we will either notify you directly, or place a notice on our privacy policy (
https://www.trafficpanic.com/privacy
) notifying you of such;
we may disclose your information to our personnel, contractors, members of our group, our holding company, and any subsidiaries of such parties. These are defined in section 1159 of the Companies Act 2006.
THIS IS WHERE WE STORE YOUR INFORMATION
All information you provide to us is stored in Google Cloud Platform (Google), MongoDB Atlas hosted within Google Cloud Platform and GameAnalytics. The destination of the data depends on the project and the Google Cloud settings, but we generally default to either the United States or Belgium.
In addition to their location, the data that we collect from you may be processed outside the European Economic Area (EEA):
By other third parties acting, as AWS, as data processors (i.e. they are processing the data only for purposes that we determine), but we have ensured that there is an adequate level of protection for such data (Biding Corporate rules or standard contractual clauses);
By third parties acting as data controller. They are listed in the tables above, and the links to their Privacy policies can lead you to more information.
We suggest that you refer to the privacy policies of those third parties (listed above in this policy).
If you’d like to find out more about the safeguards we have in place, please email
gdpr@district5.co.uk
HERE ARE YOUR RIGHTS
You have the following rights over how we process your personal data. We endeavour to respond to any request within 1 calendar month. To issue a formal request, please email
gdpr@district5.co.uk
with your device advertising identifier.
You have:
The right to opt-out and control your data for marketing purpose
The right to request a copy of your data
The right to correct your data
The right to delete your data
The right to obtain a programmatic machine readable copy of your data
The right to make a complaint to a supervisory authority
THIRD PARTY PROPERTIES ACCESSED FROM THE WEBSITE AND/OR GAME
Our Services may contain links to external services which are owned and operated by third parties. If you follow a link to any of these online properties, please note that they have their own privacy policies which will govern use of any personal data that they process and for which we can not be held responsible.
NO MARKETING TO CHILDREN
We do not knowingly advertise to children under the age of 16 or collect their personal information.
In the unlikely event that we have (or you believe we have) collected information from a child, please contact us by emailing
gdpr@district5.co.uk
where we will take all necessary steps to purge the data from our systems.
INFORMATION SECURITY
We take security seriously. As such, we take all reasonable measures and precautions to ensure any data we hold is safe. These steps include:
reducing the amount of personal data collected to a strict minimum
limiting access to specific personnel
encrypting any data in transit or storage locations.
Despite all of the precautions and preventive measures we take, no security system or precaution can be 100% secure.
CHANGES TO OUR POLICY
Any changes we may make to this Policy in the future will be posted on this page. Where it makes sense because the changes are material, we will notify you of the changes in any appropriate manner such as when you next interact with the Website or a Game.
CONTACTING US IS EASY
We really do welcome any questions, comments and requests you may have regarding this Policy. You can contact us by emailing us at
gdpr@district5.co.uk
.
We will respond to you in a timely manner but advise that it might take up to a week for a response, and up to 1 calendar month to process any data related requests.